controller

Class AbstractController<T extends EditableObject>

  • java.lang.Object
    • controller.AbstractController<T>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CommissionContainerController, CompanyController, ContractController, FleetController, FunctionController, InsuranceCompanyController, InvoiceController, RoleController, SpecialConditionController, SuretyController, UserController, VehicleInsuranceController

    public abstract class AbstractController<T extends EditableObject>
extends java.lang.Object
    This class and it's subclasses are framework independent controller classes. These classes should act as a protecting interface of the backend model.

    The methods of these classes take care of

  • Logging
  • Authorization

    • Currently there is a generic implementation for the get all , get id, update, create and archive methods.

    • Method Detail

      • isOwner

        public abstract boolean isOwner(T t,
                                Function function)
        This gets called when the role corresponding with the function has the READ_MINE/UPDATE_MINE/DELETE_MINE/CREATE_MINE action of the resource. It should determine whether the function is the "owner" of the object.
        Parameters:
        t - object that should be checked
        function - the user field of function will be used to determine if the user is the owner
        Returns:
        true if the user is authorized to perform an action on the object if it has *_MINE rights.

      • get

        public T get(java.util.UUID uuid)
      throws DataAccessException,
             UnAuthorizedException,
             ObjectNotFoundException
        Attempt to get the object of type T that has the UUID uuid
        Parameters:
        uuid - uuid of object to retrieve
        Returns:
        Object of type T corresponding with the uuid
        Throws:
        DataAccessException - something went wrong with the database
        UnAuthorizedException - The function does not have the rights to perform this operation. The object can be retrieved if the user has the READ_ALL Action of the Resource or READ_MINE and the user is the owner of the object.
        ObjectNotFoundException - no object with that id exists

      • getAll

        public java.util.Collection<T> getAll(Filter... filters)
                               throws DataAccessException,
                                      UnAuthorizedException
        Attempt to get all object of type T that pass the filters.
        Parameters:
        filters - filters where the objects should be filtered
        Returns:
        Object of type T corresponding with the uuid
        Throws:
        DataAccessException - something went wrong with the database
        UnAuthorizedException - The function does not have the rights to retrieve all of the objects that pass the filters. If there is atleast one object that the function does not have the rights to retrieve, this exception will be thrown.

        Attempt to archive the object of type T that has the UUID uuid
        Parameters:
        uuid - uuid of object to archive
        Throws:
        DataAccessException - something went wrong with the database
        UnAuthorizedException - The function does not have the rights to perform this operation. The object can be retrieved if the user has the REMOVE_ALL Action of the Resource or REMOVE_MINE and the user is the owner of the object.

      • create

        public T create(T t)
         throws DataAccessException,
                UnAuthorizedException,
                ConstraintViolationException
        Attempt to create the object t
        Parameters:
        t - the value of uuid will be ignored
        Returns:
        the same object as t, but the uuid field will now have a valid value
        Throws:
        DataAccessException - something went wrong with the database
        UnAuthorizedException - The function does not have the rights to perform this operation. The object can be created if the user has the CREATE_ALL Action of the Resource or CREATE_MINE and the user is the owner of the object.
        ConstraintViolationException - one or more fields of t are invalid

      • update

        public T update(T t)
         throws DataAccessException,
                UnAuthorizedException,
                ObjectNotFoundException,
                ConstraintViolationException
        Attempt to get the object of type T that has the UUID uuid
        Parameters:
        t - object that has to be updated. All fields can be different from what the fields are in the database except the uuid.
        Returns:
        Object of type T corresponding with the uuid
        Throws:
        DataAccessException - something went wrong with the database
        UnAuthorizedException - The function does not have the rights to perform this operation. The object can be updated if the user has the UPDATE_ALL Action of the Resource or READ_MINE and the user is the owner of the original object and the updated object.
        ObjectNotFoundException - there is no object with the same id as t.id
        ConstraintViolationException - one more fields of t are invalid
